<%# Tri-state health line for the stack pane. Beta 4 F3-D — status
    surface migrated from a colored glyph + word span to the canonical
    `Tui::ChipComponent` `[ label ]` primitive (ADR 0016 TUI design
    system). The label-to-variant mapping lives on the component; this
    template is a thin shell that lays out the label + chip on one
    flexible row, label flush left, chip flush right. Inline flex
    avoids adding a new CSS class — the layout is single-purpose to
    this row and reused across all six stack subsystem tiles. %>
<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; margin-bottom: 6px;">
  <span><strong><%= label %></strong></span>
  <%= render(Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: chip_label, variant: chip_variant)) %>
</div>
